    OutsideLabel.BoxOutsideLabel, OutsideLabel.LineLabel

    public abstract class OutsideLabel
extends Label
    This class describes labels that are on the outer perimeter of some element.

    • Method Detail

      • flip

        public void flip()
        Rotates this label sideways, i.e., swaps the width and the height of the label. The whole diagram is reordered afterwards, or at the end of the current transaction. Use the method isFlipped() to check whether the label currently is flipped.

      • isFlipped

        public boolean isFlipped()
        Checks whether the label currently is rotated.
        Returns:
        whether the label currently is rotated.

      • setAutoFlip

        public abstract void setAutoFlip(boolean state)
        Sets the auto flip parameter for this label. If auto flip is set, then the label will be always flipped sideways (its width and height swapped) when placed on a vertical segment, so that it always runs along the segment (unless flipped is set, in which case this ensures the label always runs perpendicular to the segment).
        Parameters:
        state - whether to set or unset the auto flip parameter

      • isAutoFlipped

        public boolean isAutoFlipped()
        Checks whether the auto flip parameter for this label is set.
        Returns:
        whether the auto flip parameter for this label is set.

      • resize

        public void resize(java.awt.geom.Rectangle2D.Double rectangle)
        Description copied from class: Label
        Resizes the label, moving it from its current relative position to the position defined by the given rectangle center point. Changes the minimum size of the label to the given size. The actual size may differ due to children. The whole diagram is reordered afterwards, or at the end of the current transaction.
        Parameters:
        rectangle - the new position of the label to resize it to
